In the Name of God

A photo-journalist is found dead, and his ransacked apartment suggests his killer was seeking something. When Beck's superior, Margareta Oberg, looks through the evidence, she is visibly shocked by two of the images found on the scene, and even goes so far as to hide the pictures from the team. As the investigation progresses, Martin is forced to wonder who was pictured in the two confiscated photographs? And was the motive for the murder revenge, blackmail, or something even more sinister?
